{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:02:42.768Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Investigating Related APIs**\n\nOkay, I've got a good handle on one API and I am now moving on to exploring others, specifically looking at potential patterns in the `users` and `ai-operations` APIs. I'm also now pondering the best storage strategy for the mock governance items.\n\n\n**Confirming Database Location**\n\nI've determined that `lib/api-auth.ts` is the ideal location for the mock governance database. It aligns well with the existing architecture by providing global persistence across hot reloads, since it's loaded globally and imported by relevant API routes. This maintains a clean and logical structure. I'm now examining existing fields in the TSX files for data population, considering `policies`, `oversight`, `documents`, `INITIAL_ALERTS`, and `INITIAL_POLICIES`. My next step is to examine the fields within the Python backend SQLAlchemy models, such as `id` and `client_id`.\n\n\n**Defining Governance Schema**\n\nI'm now focusing on designing the `ApiGovernanceItem` interface. I've considered how fields such as `id`, `client_id`, and `project_id` will be string/number compatible for Node, but also map back to the SQL database. I've also incorporated `title`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, `due_date`, and `description`, ensuring the interface is flexible enough to match both frontend alerts/policies and the Python models. I'm taking another pass to see if there are other useful parameters.\n\n\n**Revisiting Access Control**\n\nI'm now deep-diving back into access controls. I need to ensure client roles can only read their `client_id` data, and admin roles can manage everything. I will need to be extremely careful with client role permissions! I'm thinking I must first filter list results, but also validate *every* single ID-based request. Is the current user permitted to view the governance item? Should create, update, delete be forbidden? I also will re-examine the role check logic to ensure the correct access is always granted.\n\n\n"}}
