{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:03:34.378Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"run_commands","toolCallId":"fsw5922k","output":[{"query":"grep -rn \"governance\" automation/tasks.json","result":"automation/tasks.json:56:    \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage What We Build section. It must include these required cards: AI Strategy, AI Engineering, Agentic AI, AI Governance, AI Labs, AI Factory, AI Marketplace, AI Operations. Use existing approved card/grid design if present. Do not duplicate an existing capabilities section. Add links: AI Strategy /capabilities/strategy, AI Engineering /capabilities/engineering, Agentic AI /capabilities/agents, AI Governance /capabilities/governance, AI Labs /capabilities/labs, AI Factory /platforms/factory or /capabilities/operations, AI Marketplace /platforms/marketplace, AI Operations /capabilities/operations. Include secondary references where natural: Knowledge Graph, Data Platforms, Digital Twins, University Platforms, Managed Services. Design must be elegant, expensive, responsive, and not a generic card dump. Use subtle hover and reveal animations. No fake claims. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:144:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /capabilities and all capability subpages into a premium technical architecture design family. Do not touch landing page. Pages: /capabilities, /capabilities/strategy, /capabilities/engineering, /capabilities/agents, /capabilities/governance, /capabilities/data, /capabilities/labs, /capabilities/operations, /capabilities/twins, /capabilities/universities, /capabilities/knowledge-graph, /capabilities/managed-services. Design mood: technical, architectural, systems-driven, precise, credible, expensive. Build a unique capabilities landing page with capability command grid, enterprise AI stack, Agent Factory and Knowledge Graph Factory visual, Garage-to-Factory mapping, related platforms, and CTA. Subpages must share a coherent family template but feel tailored through unique hero visuals, use-case grids, architecture diagrams, delivery model panels, business outcome sections, tabs or carousels where helpful, and related platforms/industries. Use SVG/CSS architecture visuals with layers such as Experience Layer, Agentic AI Layer, Knowledge Graph Layer, Data and Integration Layer, Governance Layer, Managed AI Operations Layer. Use Framer Motion and Aceternity-inspired bento, spotlight, moving-border, sticky reveal, or tab patterns if lightweight. Do not make legal/compliance/ROI guarantees. No fake clients or dashboards. Mobile excellent. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:176:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /industries/energy, /industries/telecom, /industries/government, and /industries/public-sector using the premium industry family design. Do not touch landing page. Energy challenges: asset operations, field service, regulatory documentation, grid or plant knowledge, operational optimization. Telecom challenges: network operations, customer service, field operations, knowledge fragmentation, service delivery visibility. Government/Public Sector challenges: citizen services, policy search, case workflows, documentation, transparency and governance. Suggested agents: Asset Operations Agent, Field Service Copilot, Document Intelligence Agent, Knowledge Search Agent, Executive Dashboard Agent, Network Operations Copilot, Customer Experience Agent, Citizen Service Agent, Policy Intelligence Agent, Case Triage Agent. Related platforms: TelecomVerse, Control Center, Runtime Governance. Avoid government or compliance guarantees. No fake clients, fake agencies, or fake metrics. Include rich visuals, tabs/carousels, architecture panels, and mobile responsive layouts. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:192:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms, /platforms/garage, /platforms/foundry, and /platforms/factory into premium enterprise software product pages. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: productized assets, platform stack, enterprise software, control systems, expensive. /platforms should include hero, platform grid, Garage Foundry Factory product stack, industry mesh platforms, control/governance layer, and CTA. Garage page must include Discover AI, Workshops, AI Labs, Experiment Zone and describe innovation layer. Foundry must include Build Agents, Runtime, Data Fabric, AI Engineering and describe co-creation layer. Factory must include Scale, Monitor, Operate, Monetize and describe industrialisation layer. Use product OS visuals, module cards, workflow diagrams, sticky scroll or tabs, carousel where useful, SVG/CSS product previews, Framer Motion if available, Aceternity-inspired bento/spotlight/moving-border patterns. No fake screenshots, fake metrics, or fake pricing. Mobile excellent. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:200:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms/blueprint, /platforms/marketplace, and /platforms/control-center as premium enterprise product pages. Do not touch landing page. Blueprint page: explain enterprise AI blueprints, readiness scoring, solution recommendations, expected impact, 90-day roadmap, and link to /build/blueprint. Marketplace page: curated agent patterns and accelerators, no fake purchasable products or pricing. Control Center page: monitor AI programs, agent health, spend, adoption, governance, delivery operations, but no fake live metrics. Use product-grade hero visuals, tabs, carousels, dashboard-style preview panels without fake numbers, architecture diagrams, and CTAs. Make each page unique while sharing platform family design. Use Framer Motion and local Aceternity-inspired effects if available. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:224:    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /platforms/agent-marketplace, /platforms/runtime-governance, and /platforms/developer-platform. Do not touch landing page. Agent Marketplace should feel like a catalog of reusable enterprise agent patterns: knowledge agents, operations agents, compliance agents, customer experience agents, executive agents, document intelligence agents. Runtime Governance should focus on agent behavior, human oversight, permissions, monitoring, risk controls, auditability, and governance-first design without guaranteeing compliance. Developer Platform should feel like a developer-facing surface for building, testing, integrating, and operating enterprise agents, but no fake API keys or fake docs. Use product pages with tabs, carousels, technical diagrams, code-like visual blocks that are clearly illustrative, and strong CTAs. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:432:    \"prompt\": \"Add a safe simulated agent preview inside /build/sandbox. Do not touch landing page. When a user selects a demo agent, show a deterministic, local, prewritten workflow simulation: user challenge, agent interpretation, knowledge needed, actions it would take, human approval point, governance check, and expected output preview. Make it clear this is a static frontend simulation and not a live AI agent. No API calls. No fake real-time claims. Use a premium step-by-step timeline, animated workflow path, or tabbed execution viewer. Add related CTAs to Talk to Agent, Blueprint, and Foundry Studio. Mobile and accessibility must be excellent. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:560:    \"prompt\": \"This is the first task of Phase 4. Do not edit files. Audit the current implementation for all login, client portal, admin portal, and private workspace related routes and components. Inspect app/portal, app/client, app/admin if present, app/login if present, app/layout.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/CommandCenter.tsx, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, and any existing dashboard, portal, auth, client, admin, table, document, billing, support, analytics, or governance components. Determine what currently exists as a public shell and what is missing for a proper logged-in product experience. Do not create backend, real auth, database, AWS, email, OTP, payment, upload, or API integrations. Produce a detailed implementation gap report for Phase 4 frontend. The report must cover required routes, app shell, local auth preview, role switching, route protection preview, client portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, admin dashboard, client management, user management, project management, documents admin, billing admin, support admin, analytics admin, governance admin, activity feed, notifications, global search, command center, tables, filters, mobile UX, accessibility, design system, and final QA. Final response must include files inspected, existing capabilities, missing routes, missing components, design risks, and recommended implementation order. Do not edit files.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:576:    \"prompt\": \"Create or verify explicit App Router pages for the full Phase 4 route structure. Do not use slug routing. Do not create app/[...slug]/page.tsx. Do not recreate PublicRoutePage. Do not touch the landing page. Required public entry routes: /login, /portal, /portal/login. Required client portal routes: /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/projects/[id] if the current project supports dynamic explicit folders safely, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/ai-operations/[id] if safe, /portal/documents, /portal/documents/[id] if safe, /portal/billing, /portal/billing/invoices, /portal/billing/invoices/[id] if safe, /portal/support, /portal/support/[id] if safe, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /portal/settings, /portal/activity. Required compatibility client routes: /client, /client/control-center, /client/dashboard if useful. Required admin routes: /admin, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/clients/[id] if safe, /admin/projects, /admin/projects/[id] if safe, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance, /admin/settings, /admin/activity. If dynamic routes are risky in the current automation, create explicit list/detail pages without dynamic params and use local state/detail drawers instead. Pages may initially render shared shell placeholders, but every route must exist explicitly. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:624:    \"prompt\": \"Data should support dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing/invoices, support tickets, governance, users, and clients. Include types for ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem, User, Role.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:656:    \"prompt\": \"Build /portal/ai-operations as the client-facing AI operations command center. Do not touch landing page. Include agent health overview, managed AI operations status, active agents,governance checks, runtime status and Control Center link. Use labels and representative preview data only. Do not claim real-time operations. Use premium dashboard UI with status rails, agent cards, health rings, timeline, and tabs. Add filters by project, agent type, status, and operating stage. No backend. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:683:    \"id\": \"91-phase4-client-governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:686:    \"target\": \"/portal/governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:688:    \"prompt\": \"Build /portal/governance as a premium governance workspace. Do not touch landing page. Include governance overview, policy items, human oversight points, AI operation governance checks, document governance. Do not make legal or compliance guarantees. Use language like designed to support governance workflows. Include filters by project, agent, status, and severity. No backend. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:696:    \"prompt\": \"Build /admin and /admin/dashboard as the GFF internal admin control center. Do not touch landing page. Use the private app shell with admin navigation. The dashboard should include clients overview, active projects, AI operations overview, pending support tickets, billing status, governance alerts. Use representative preview data only. No backend. No fake live metrics. The admin dashboard should feel powerful, dense but elegant, and built for internal delivery operations. Use bento layout, command actions, data cards, and strong navigation. Mobile must remain usable. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:728:    \"prompt\": \"Build /admin/ai-operations as internal AI operations command center. Do not touch landing page. Include all client agent operations, agent health, governance alerts,project links, and owner assignment. Add filters by client, project, agent type, status, severity, owner. Add local-only actions: assign owner. Do not claim live runtime or real monitoring. Use premium observability UI with status rails, health cards, tables, and detail drawer. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:736:    \"prompt\": \"Build /admin/documents as internal document management preview. Do not touch landing page. Include all documents across clients/projects with search, filters by client, project, type, status, owner, version. Add assign document to project. No real upload, no storage, no download. Use document drawer with metadata, related project, and governance status. Premium admin UI, mobile card fallback. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:755:    \"id\": \"105-phase4-admin-governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:758:    \"target\": \"/admin/governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:760:    \"prompt\": \"Build /admin/governance as internal governance management. Do not touch landing page. Include governance items across clients/projects/agents, risk severity, owner, status, due date, s. Do not guarantee compliance. Use local-only actions: assign reviewer. Premium governance console UI with filters, cards, and detail drawer. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:776:    \"prompt\": \"Perform a mobile UX pass for all login, portal, client, and admin routes. Do not touch landing page. Fix only mobile and responsive issues. Check /login, /portal, /portal/login, /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/documents, /portal/billing, /portal/support, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/projects, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance. Ensure no horizontal overflow, sidebar works on mobile, topbar is usable, tables become cards, filters collapse, modals/drawers fit, charts are readable, buttons are tappable, and forms are easy to use. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:856:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP database models for the admin and client portal only. Do not create models for GFF AI tools such as Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, or Foundry Studio. Required models: User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem. Use simple fields that support the Phase 4 UI. User fields: id, name, email, hashed_password, role, client_id nullable, status, created_at, updated_at. Roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin. ClientAccount fields: id, name, industry, region, status, account_owner, created_at. Project fields: id, client_id, name, phase, status, health, owner, start_date, target_date, progress, description. AgentOperation fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, name, agent_type, status, health, owner, governance_status, last_activity_at. DocumentItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, document_type, status, version, owner, visibility, created_at. Invoice fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, invoice_number, status, amount, currency, due_date, issued_date. SupportTicket fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, category, priority, status, assigned_to, created_by, description, created_at. GovernanceItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, severity, status, owner, due_date, description. Keep relationships simple. Run backend import check.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:880:    \"prompt\": \"Implement simple RBAC helpers for the MVP backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin. Define permission groups: client_portal_access, admin_access, manage_clients, manage_users, manage_projects, manage_ai_operations, manage_documents, manage_billing, manage_support, manage_governance, view_analytics. Implement FastAPI dependencies such as get_current_user, require_roles, require_admin, require_client_access, require_same_client_or_admin. Client users must only access their own client_id data. Admin roles can access all data depending on permission. Keep this simple and explicit. Do not overbuild enterprise permissions yet. Run backend checks.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:896:    \"prompt\": \"Create a safe local seed script for MVP backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed representative data only. Create dev users for roles: gff_admin, client_admin, client_member. Use simple documented local passwords such as password123 only in dev seed documentation. Create 2 to 3 representative client accounts, several projects, agent operations, documents metadata, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Do not use real client names or fake logos. Ensure seed script can be run repeatedly without duplicating data, either by checking existing emails/records or resetting safely with explicit command. Add README instructions. Run seed if safe and verify backend can start.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:936:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP AI Operations APIs under /api/v1/ai-operations. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This is only for portal/admin AI operations records, not live GFF AI tool execution. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, DELETE or archive. Admin roles can manage all. Client roles can read only records for their client_id. Include filters: client_id, project_id, status, health, agent_type, governance_status, owner. No real agent runtime, no live monitoring, no external AI calls. Use representative database records only.  Run backend checks.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:963:    \"id\": \"140-phase5-api-governance-crud\",\nautomation/tasks.json:966:    \"target\": \"governance APIs\",\nautomation/tasks.json:968:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP governance APIs under /api/v1/governance. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, PATCH status, DELETE or archive. Admin roles can manage all. Client roles can read their client_id governance items and optionally  if the Phase 4 UI already supports local preview. No legal/compliance guarantees. Include filters: client_id, project_id, severity, status, owner, due date, search.  Run backend checks.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:976:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP dashboard summary APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/dashboard/client for client portal summary and GET /api/v1/dashboard/admin for admin summary. Client dashboard should return counts and recent records for that user's client_id: active projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, open support tickets, governance items. Admin dashboard should return global counts and recent records across clients: clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance Values must come from local database records, not hardcoded frontend mock data. Keep queries simple. Run backend checks.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:984:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP analytics APIs under /api/v1/analytics. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/analytics/client and GET /api/v1/analytics/admin. Use database aggregation from projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Keep it simple: counts by status, counts by phase, support by priority, invoice by status, AI operations by health, governance by severity. No fake live analytics. No external analytics provider. Client roles see only their client_id data. Admin roles see all. Run backend checks.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1008:    \"prompt\": \"Create a frontend API client for portal/admin backend integration. Do not touch landing page. Do not connect GFF AI tools to backend. The API client should support base URL from NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL defaulting to local backend, bearer token handling, JSON request helpers, typed functions, error handling, and logout on unauthorized if safe. Add modules for auth, dashboard, clients, users, projects, aiOperations, documents, invoices, support, governance, analytics. Keep it small and readable. Do not use axios unless already used; fetch is fine. Ensure code is client-safe and does not break SSR. Run frontend lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1032:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/dashboard to the MVP backend dashboard API. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static mock dashboard data with data fetched from /api/v1/dashboard/client when authenticated. Keep graceful loading, error, empty, and offline/dev fallback states. Use the existing premium Phase 4 UI and preserve its design. Do not redesign. Ensure data is client-scoped by backend. Widgets: projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, analytics, governance. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1075:    \"id\": \"156-phase5-frontend-client-analytics-governance-api\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1078:    \"target\": \"/portal/analytics and /portal/governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1080:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/analytics to /api/v1/analytics/client and /portal/governance to /api/v1/governance. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static data with backend summaries and governance records. Governance read actions may be backend-connected if endpoint exists, otherwise keep read-only. Preserve Phase 4 visual design, charts, filters, and mobile behavior. Add loading, empty, error, and retry states. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1088:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin and /admin/dashboard to backend /api/v1/dashboard/admin. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static admin dashboard data with backend data. Preserve Phase 4 premium admin UI. Add loading, empty, error, retry states. Admin dashboard should show clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance,  based on database records. No fake live data. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1104:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/projects and /admin/ai-operations to backend CRUD APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin projects page should list, filter, create, edit, archive projects if API supports it. Admin AI operations page should list, filter, create, edit, assign owner, update status/health/governance if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 UI with drawers/modals. No live agent runtime. Add loading, empty, error, success states. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1115:    \"id\": \"162-phase5-frontend-admin-support-governance-api\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1118:    \"target\": \"/admin/support and /admin/governance\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1120:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/support to backend support ticket APIs and /admin/governance to backend governance APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin support should list, filter, assign, update status, and optionally add local/backend comment depending on API. Admin governance should list, filter, create, update status, assign reviewer if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 premium UI. No email, no attachments, no compliance guarantees. Add loading, empty, error, success, retry states. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1128:    \"prompt\": \"Reduce reliance on Phase 4 local mock data for portal/admin pages now connected to backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Keep local mock data only as fallback or for non-backend preview sections. Portal/admin dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance,clients, and users should prefer backend API data. Do not delete shared mock data if still used safely by non-integrated components, but clearly separate backend-connected data from fallback data. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1168:    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend exists and runs. Verify SQLite database setup. Verify seed data and dev users. Verify JWT login, auth/me, logout, RBAC, client data scoping, admin access. Verify CRUD APIs for clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, invoices metadata, support tickets, governance, dashboard summaries, analytics summaries. Verify frontend login connects to backend. Verify client portal pages use backend data: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Verify admin pages use backend data: Dashboard, Clients, Users, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Verify no AWS, storage, payment, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth, or backend for GFF AI tools was added. Verify landing page unchanged. Run backend tests/checks if available, backend startup/import checks, npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, local dev login credentials from seed docs, and TODOs for Phase 6 production hardening.\"\n","success":true}],"durationMs":12}}
