{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:04:21.727Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Perfecting API Structure**\n\nI've hit a breakthrough. The structure for the API routes is ideal. Having dedicated files for list retrieval/creation, individual resource management, and separate handling for status updates is precisely what's needed. It's perfectly parallel!\n\n\n**Refining API Endpoints**\n\nI'm now integrating the governance API specifications. Specifically, `/api/v1/governance` is the designated space. I'm focusing on defining the endpoints for GET list, GET by ID, POST create, PATCH update, PATCH status, and DELETE/archive, ensuring admin roles can manage everything. I'm also addressing client role access based on client ID. Filters like client_id, project_id, severity, and more are also being incorporated. Mock data design is underway, focusing on the `ApiGovernanceItem` interface and mock items matching client IDs.\n\n\n**Mapping Data Elements**\n\nI'm translating the data elements into a structured format. The aim is a perfect fit with the `governance_items` model, ensuring complete compatibility. I'm focusing on aligning the new data with the existing fields, focusing on how `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, and `due_date` all fit within the `/backend/app/models/governance_item.py` model. I have to make sure each attribute, like the array of log strings, is properly managed.\n\n\n**Defining Data Interfaces**\n\nI've crafted the `ApiGovernanceItem` interface. It aligns perfectly with the backend and frontend requirements. It includes required and optional fields to handle all data, including `id`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, and `severity`. I've added flexible status options and date formatting for full compatibility. Optional fields like `logs` and `lastUpdated` are included for frontend functionality.\n\n\n**Populating Initial Data**\n\nI'm now populating the initial state with mock items, ensuring they fit the defined `ApiGovernanceItem` interface and align with backend structures. I've focused on client associations within `lib/api-auth.ts`, incorporating client names like \"Apex Sovereign Group\" and \"Global Retail Enclave\" to match mock data. I am working on how to create the `DEFAULT_API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE` items. The data includes titles, IDs, and client-project associations such as \"proj-001\" and \"APEX-SEC\".\n\n\n**Constructing Item Details**\n\nI'm now integrating detailed governance item data, like the logs and descriptions, focusing on aligning them with the established `ApiGovernanceItem` interface. I'm taking a close look at a critical item with a \"Critical\" severity, \"Under Review\" status, and various log entries. I'm focusing on ensuring data consistency. The integration of `hash` and `lastUpdated` attributes is ongoing.\n\n\n**Integrating Item Details**\n\nI'm now integrating item details based on specific examples. The focus is ensuring the data perfectly fits the `ApiGovernanceItem` interface. I'm incorporating detailed information such as \"Global Retail Real-Time Audit Ring\" with \"High\" severity and \"Flagged\" status. I'm also addressing the inclusion of the 'logs', including those critical system messages. The `due_date` and `lastUpdated` attributes are being carefully assessed for compatibility.\n\n\n**Refining Item Integration**\n\nI'm now focusing on integrating a complex governance item. My goal is to ensure data integrity and full alignment with the `ApiGovernanceItem` interface. I'm focusing on attributes like severity, status, due_date, and logs. Specifically, I'm examining a \"Medium\" severity item with \"Flagged\" status, owned by \"Evelyn Carter\". The logs and description, along with the timestamps, all need to fit perfectly.\n\n\n\n**Generating Unique IDs**\n\nI'm now implementing the `getNextGovernanceId` function. I've ensured it generates unique IDs by parsing existing IDs, finding the maximum, and incrementing. I'm focusing on the formatting of the new IDs to ensure they match the established \"gov-XXX\" pattern, including leading zeros. This ensures proper data integrity. I am now working on understanding how these new checks and functions might impact the existing data model, and what new tests will be required.\n\n\n**Clarifying Backend Connections**\n\nI'm now investigating backend integration. I need to understand whether to create Python endpoints in `/backend/app/api/routes` or use existing validation scripts. I'm examining `/backend/app/api/routes/clients.py` for Python endpoint implementation examples. I am now looking at the FastAPI backend and NextJS server and how they might interact, understanding their individual roles.\n\n\n"}}
