{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:06:17.894Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Code Completion**\n\nThe `lib/api-auth.ts` modifications are done and ready to go. Now, I'm setting my sights on crafting `app/api/v1/governance/route.ts`. The plan is to build out standard GET support for filtering by `client_id`, `project_id`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, and `due`.\n\n\n**Developing GET Filter Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the GET filter logic within `app/api/v1/governance/route.ts`, focusing on robust parameter handling. I'm prioritizing the `client_id`, `project_id`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, `due_date`, and `search` filters, including variants of the `due_date` parameter to accommodate different naming conventions. I'm considering backend checks to ensure the security of filters.\n\n\n**Implementing Filter Enforcement**\n\nI'm now incorporating client boundary enforcement into the filtering process. For non-admin users, I'm ensuring they can only access data associated with their own `client_id`. I've implemented a check to block access to other client data. For admin users, I've enabled filtering by `client_id`, `project_id`, `severity`, `status`, and `owner`. I've also added checks to ensure parameter sanitation.\n\n\n**Refining Date & Search**\n\nI'm making it so we handle different `due date` parameter variations gracefully. I want to standardize on the `due_date` format internally, but I'm accounting for inputs like `dueDate` and `due-date`. Also, I'm now polishing up the search functionality, considering various fields for broader matching, which includes `title`, `description`, `owner`, `id`, and potentially the `standard` fields. I am ready to move to the POST request.\n\n\n**Validating POST Request Body**\n\nI'm now focusing on validating the POST request body within `app/api/v1/governance/route.ts`. I'm making sure all required fields are present and of the correct type, like `title` and `client_id`, returning a 400 error with descriptive messages if validation fails. I'm also including client ID validation against a defined list.\n\n\n**Generating Hash Efficiently**\n\nI've decided to streamline the hash generation for POST requests. I'm choosing `Math.random().toString(16).substring(2, 10).toUpperCase()` over `crypto` to avoid potential import issues and for its efficiency. The existing `api-auth.ts` imports were a red herring; this approach simplifies the logic without sacrificing security. I'm confirming that the method returns a string in hexadecimal format. Now, I'm checking the implementation of `getAuthCaller` to ensure that it has the relevant caller properties.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:06:17.897Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"qpi1x5xb","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/governance/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE, \n  API_MOCK_PROJECTS,\n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiGovernanceItem, \n  getNextGovernanceId, \n  getClientNameFromId, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const projectIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"project_id\");\n    const severityFilter = searchParams.get(\"severity\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const ownerFilter = searchParams.get(\"owner\");\n    const dueDateFilter = searchParams.get(\"due_date\") || searchParams.get(\"due-date\") || searchParams.get(\"dueDate\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let items = Object.values(API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE) as ApiGovernanceItem[];\n\n    // RBAC policy logic: client roles can only read their own client_id items\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      items = items.filter(item => item.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Enforce client boundaries\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's governance data.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filters\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        items = items.filter(item => item.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply specific filters\n    if (projectIdFilter) {\n      const q = projectIdFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => item.project_id && item.project_id.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (severityFilter) {\n      const q = severityFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => item.severity.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => item.status.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (ownerFilter) {\n      const q = ownerFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => item.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (dueDateFilter) {\n      const q = dueDateFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => item.due_date.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      items = items.filter(item => \n        item.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        item.description.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        item.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        item.id.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        (item.standard && item.standard.toLowerCase().includes(q))\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, governance: items });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    // MVP constraints: admin create/update/delete only\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can create governance items.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { title, client_id, project_id, severity, status, owner, due_date, description, standard, nodeId, hash, logs } = body;\n\n    if (!title || typeof title !== \"string\" || !title.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'title' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!client_id || typeof client_id !== \"string\" || !client_id.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'client_id' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n    if (!validClients.includes(client_id)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid 'client_id' specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const newGovId = getNextGovernanceId();\n    \n    // Resolve project name if project_id is supplied\n    let projName: string | undefined = undefined;\n    if (project_id) {\n      const proj = (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as any)[project_id];\n      if (proj) projName = proj.name;\n    }\n\n    const newGovItem: ApiGovernanceItem = {\n      id: newGovId,\n      title: title.trim(),\n      client_id: client_id,\n      client_name: getClientNameFromId(client_id),\n      project_id: project_id || undefined,\n      project_name: projName,\n      severity: severity || \"Low\",\n      status: status || \"active\",\n      owner: owner || caller.name,\n      due_date: due_date || new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],\n      description: description || \"\",\n      standard: standard || \"ISO-27001\",\n      nodeId: nodeId || undefined,\n      hash: hash || \"0x\" + Math.random().toString(16).substring(2, 10).toUpperCase(),\n      logs: logs || [\"Governance item initialized in the system.\"],\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    (API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE as Record<string, ApiGovernanceItem>)[newGovId] = newGovItem;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, governance: newGovItem }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
