{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:08:23.136Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"mi7syor6","input":{"summary":"Designed and implemented robust MVP Governance CRUD API endpoints under `/api/v1/governance`.\n\n1. **Database Schema & Seed Data Extension (`lib/api-auth.ts`)**:\n   - Defined `ApiGovernanceItem` interface incorporating all requirements: standard governance attributes matching both the frontend schema structure and the Python SQLAlchemy definition (`id`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, `due_date`, `description`) as well as extended parameters for UI integration (`nodeId`, `standard`, `hash`, `logs`, `lastUpdated`).\n   - Populated the in-memory database (`API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE`) with high-fidelity compliant mock items representing real-world edge anomalies (like eBPF packet leaks and cryptographic rotation delay) and mapped them to sandbox client IDs (`client-001`, `client-002`, `client-004`).\n   - Created the auto-increment ID generation utility `getNextGovernanceId()`.\n\n2. **Collection Routing Endpoint (`app/api/v1/governance/route.ts`)**:\n   - Implemented `GET` route supporting list querying and filtering for: `client_id`, `project_id`, `severity`, `status`, `owner`, `due_date`, and generic text `search`.\n   - Built strict multi-tenancy tenant isolation logic: If the caller does not hold the platform admin role (`gff_admin`), they can only read records mapped to their specific `client_id` (retrieved via decoded token `clientAssociation`). Attempts to search or query other clients return a `403 Forbidden` response.\n   - Implemented `POST` route to initialize new governance entries with validation constraints, restricted exclusively to platform administrators.\n\n3. **Resource Routing Endpoint (`app/api/v1/governance/[id]/route.ts`)**:\n   - Implemented `GET` route to retrieve single governance item by ID, with tenant protection logic returning `403 Forbidden` if a non-admin user attempts cross-client access.\n   - Implemented `PATCH` route supporting comprehensive field modifications, restricted to admins.\n   - Implemented `DELETE` route supporting hard delete from mock store, restricted to admins.\n\n4. **Action-Specific Routing Endpoint (`app/api/v1/governance/[id]/status/route.ts`)**:\n   - Implemented standard parallel `PATCH` status action route to allow updating only the status field, restricted to administrators.\n\n5. **Automated End-to-End Verification (`scripts/test-governance-apis.js`)**:\n   - Created a dedicated compile-and-test execution script that targets our newly written routes. It verifies session authentication checks, multi-tenancy context isolation boundaries, parameter filters (`search`, `project_id`, `severity`, `due_date`), detail queries, admin-restricted write access restrictions, update mutations, status actions, and deletion flows. All operations passed successfully.","verified":true}}}
